'''''Blue Angels: Formation Flight Simulation''''' is a 1989 video game developed by [[Artech Digital Entertainment|Artech]] and published by [[Accolade (company)|Accolade]].

==Gameplay==
''Blue Angels'' is a flight simulator.<ref name=cgw150/>

==Reception==
Lt. H. E. Dille reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "''Blue Angels'' deserves a fair amount of consideration based on novelty alone. As such, the product is recommended, with [...] reservations, to PC pilots seeking a change of pace."<ref name="CGW70">{{cite magazine |last=Dille |first=Lt. H. E. |title=The NAVY'S ANGELS: Accolade's Formation Flight Simulation |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=April 1990 |volume=1 |issue=70 |pages=50, 52}}</ref>

